body_html:
I looked at this one and have a fix for it here (you could merge that commit to unblock):
guschmue@bbbb7a7

The problem is that the boosted_tree kernels build in core/kernels but they do depend on the .pb.h which are generated in tf_python_protos_cc.vcxproj but core/kernels do not depend on tf_python_protos_cc.vcxproj.

The commit above moves this protoc for boosted_tree to core so they are there when core/kernels needs them. I have not send a pr for this because there are some issues with the boosted_tree unit tests that I wanted to fix at the same time ... just not found time yet.

The reason why ci.tensorflow.org does not see this: msbuild there builds 32 projects in parallel and it just happens that tf_python_protos_cc.vcxproj is done before core/kernels needs it.

@mrry - should I send a pr for this?
